Brazil Stock Movers: Brookfield, JBS, MMX Mineracao & Metalicos

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-08-31T21:08:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/brazil-stock-movers-brookfield-jbs-mmx-mineracao-metalicos.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 12:14 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index rose 2 percent to 56,495.12.  Brookfield Incorporacoes SA (BISA3)  (BISA3 BS),  Brazil ’s fourth-
largest real-estate company by revenue, surged 5.9 percent to 7
reais, its highest price in more than a month, on speculation
that Brazil’s central bank will cut  interest rates . The bank is
scheduled to finish its two-day policy meeting this evening.  JBS SA (JBSS3)  (JBSS3 BS) gained 4.7 percent to 4.27 reais after
the world’s biggest beef producer said it plans to consolidate
its Brazilian operations into fewer units to reduce costs. The
meatpacker said it expects to save 200 million reais ($126
million) by halting its Presidente Epitacio plant in Sao Paulo
state and transferring some operations from five other Brazil
units to different plants.  MMX Mineracao & Metalicos SA (MMXM3 BS), the iron-ore miner
controlled by Brazilian billionaire  Eike Batista , advanced 4
percent to 8.12 reais as metal prices rose. Sixty-two percent
iron ore delivered to the Chinese port of Tianjin increased 0.6
percent to $179.90 a metric ton, according to the Steel Index.  To contact the reporter on this story:
